# 2. 姉からの贈り物

Mizuki: Humhumhuum♪
Mizuki: (This package is huge! What on earth did Sis send me?)
Mizuki: Whoa...! It's full of clothes!!
Mizuki: Oh, she must've made these! Wow... It's cool to see that she can make stuff like this now!
Mizuki: You can tell that this young designer making a name for herself abroad has the right stuff♪
Mizuki: Hm? There's something else really deep down... What is this?
Mizuki: Whoa, this ribbon's so pretty...!
Mizuki: Hm? A greeting card...? Let's have a look...
Greeting Card: <To Mizuki, the cutest person in the world>
Mizuki: Hehe. Oh, Sis. “Cutest” might be a bit much...
Mizuki: But since she sent this to me, I think I'll try it on♪
Mizuki: Yup, she's right... I do definitely look cute!
Mizuki: (But this ribbon and all these clothes... It's like she's written her signature on all of them...)
Mizuki: (It's great to see that Sis is having fun over there...)
Mizuki: Hey, she even sent snacks! These are just as cute and colorful...
Mizuki: (Oh, come to think of it... Miku and the others might really like it if I shared some of this candy with them.)
Mizuki: Alright, I'll take some of these over to them! They'll probably love it too since they came from overseas♪
Mizuki: So, here we go!!
Mizuki: Let's see. Where are Miku and the...?
Luka: Ready, Miku?
Miku: Ready...!
Luka: Rock! Paper! Scissors! Look over there♪
Miku: Look over... Oh...
Luka: Look over here♪
Miku: Uh... Uhh...
Luka: Hehe. I guess you can't help but look the same way I point my finger, Miku.
Miku: O-Once more time...!
Mizuki: Haha... Luka's such a meanie. Hey, over here!
Miku: Oh, Mizuki...
Luka: Oh, welcome. Just you today?
Mizuki: Yup! I was sent some snacks you don't see very often and decided to share them with you guys!
Miku: Snacks... Rin and Len might like that.
Luka: Hehe. Yes, they might. Oh...?
Luka: Mizuki, that ribbon looks lovely on you. Is it new? Did you just buy it?
Mizuki: Oh, this came with the snacks. My big sis sent it to me.
Miku: Your big sister...?
Mizuki: Yeah, I have a big sister who's much older than me. She's still just starting out, but she's a fashion designer.
Mizuki: She's living abroad right now and has it kinda tough right now... But she's working really hard towards achieving her dream of owning her own business.
Miku: I see...
Luka: Her own business overseas...? That's very ambitious of her. Has she been living abroad long?
Mizuki: Hmm... Yeah, I'd say pretty long... She moved right around the time I joined N25.
Miku: When you joined N25, Mizuki...?
Luka: Speaking of which...
Luka: Kanade and Mafuyu told us a story about how N25 initially came to be, but we didn't get to hear about when you and Ena joined, Mizuki.
Mizuki: Yeah, that's right. The timing felt a bit off to get into that, you know...?
Luka: Would you mind telling us about that? I'm sure Miku's already bored of playing rock paper scissors.
Miku: I'm not bored, but... I'd also like to hear more about that, Mizuki.
Mizuki: Wait, you do? I mean, it's really not that interesting...
Mizuki: Haha... I can't really say no to these faces, can I?
Mizuki: Alright... I'll try going in order, starting with around the time I was in my last year of junior high.
Mizuki: I really had a lot on my mind back then...
Mizuki: That was when I heard one of Kanade's songs and decided that I wanted to start making music videos.
Miku: You had a lot on your mind...?
Mizuki: Yeah... We're talking about A LOT...
Mizuki: (Things were so hard back then...)
Principal: “Ahem. Good morning, everyone. The cherry blossoms lined up near our school are all in full bloom, and it gives me great pleasure to welcome in a new school year.”
Mizuki: (*Yawn* Another boring opening ceremony...)
Mizuki: (It's always such a pain to have to start again in a completely new class. So is dealing with the first years.)
Student A: Hey, isn't that the person they were talking about...?
Student B: Yeah, maybe. The description my big brother gave me seems pretty close.
Mizuki: (Not again...)
Mizuki: (Ugh... I would've been able to ditch if the teachers hadn't found me.)
Mizuki: (I guess I can just head up to the rooftop after this. Rui's also probably pretty bored and...)
Mizuki: Oh...
Mizuki: (Right. He graduated...)
Principal: “That concludes this speech. Everyone, let's all do our best to make the most of this school year.”
Student A: Hey, let's try talking to that person!
Student B: Yeah, they seem like fun.
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: Finally, some alone time...
Mizuki: This place really is nice and quiet...
Mizuki: (It's nice and quiet, but...)
Rui: Hello, Mizuki!
Rui: Hehehe. I just thought up a wonderful idea for an effect. Would you like to hear?
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: I didn't mind a little noise...
Mizuki: (However, before Rui started coming up here, this was normal...)
Mizuki: (So, it's like nothing's changed...)
Mizuki: I'm back to square one.
Mizuki: *Sigh* Another dull day at school.
Mizuki: And another dull year that I have to survive...
Mizuki: But it's not like there's anything I can do about that.
Mizuki: Wait, MiraMagi's on today! I have to watch it as it airs!
Mizuki: (The final episode's also coming up... Man, I really don't want to see this show end.)
Mizuki: (Despite it being an evening children's anime, it has such a good story. Not only that, the characters are cute and people always write great comments about this show on forums...)
Mizuki: (And above all else, the protagonist's enemy and rival, Mia, is just too adorable!)
Mizuki: Hehe... I can't wait to see what the finale's like!
Mizuki: Oh, also. I heard that they're gonna do some promos and stuff to get everyone excited about it.
Mizuki: Yeah, here we go...! The “Let's Root For MiraMagi Together” promotional campaign!
Mizuki: Hey, we're allowed to make videos for this. I might just have to take a crack at it!
Mizuki: Alright, lemme just turn on my PC... And I can give that effect plugin I bought the other day a try.
Mizuki: (I started doing this to kill time when I'm bored, but I'm really glad that I started making my own videos...)
Mizuki: (I get to choose whatever music, assets, effects and everything else I like while also being able to edit it however I please. Not only that, it lets me focus in a way that I can block out all unnecessary distractions.)
Mizuki: (Before I entered junior high, I made my own clothes and accessories...)
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: Anyway, how should I do this...? I could try creating a montage of all the best scenes up to this point...
Mizuki's Sister's Voice: Mizuki, do you have a minute...?
Mizuki: Hm? Yeah, sure.
Mizuki's Sister: Okay, I'm coming in. Hm...?
Mizuki's Sister: Oh, are you making a MiaMagic video? You really do love that show, don't you?
Mizuki: Sis, it's not “MiaMagic”. It's called “MiraMagi”! Or “Miracle Magic Girl ☆ Lala”! The animated epic about Lala, the magical girl who's fighting to save the day, that's all the rage right now!
Mizuki: While Mia's the girl who's her enemy and rival, so please don't get them mixed up!
Mizuki's Sister: Ah, right. Yes. Haha. I'm sorry, Mizuki. I must've gotten them mixed up since you seem to really enjoy talking about Mia.
Mizuki: To be fair, it is kinda confusing... Anyway, did you need something from me?
Mizuki's Sister: Oh, I was just packing up my things and found all these clothes that I'd made in the past. Would you like them, Mizuki? They're all in this box.
Mizuki: Wait, really? Can I see?!
Mizuki: Whoa, you used to make this kind of stuff...?! You really are an amazing designer!
Mizuki's Sister: Hehe. Thanks. Although, my fashion school teachers didn't really like this one.
Mizuki: But the ones at that school in France called you a genius, right?!
Mizuki's Sister: A genius...? I really don't think I was called that, but...
Mizuki's Sister: Over here, my teachers would say that my designs were “far too radical” without even really looking at what I'd drawn. I was even turned away by so many others when it came time to look for a job...
Mizuki's Sister: Which is why I was so happy when I discovered peers who believed the opposite of them.
Mizuki: Yeah, I know you went through a lot and had to work really hard... But I'm also happy that they acknowledged your talents!
Mizuki: So, Sis, good luck over there!
Mizuki's Sister: Hehe. Aren't you getting a little ahead of yourself? I'm not leaving until next month.
Mizuki's Sister: Still, Mizuki, thank you.
Mizuki's Sister: ... By the way... How have you been recently...?
Mizuki: Me? Um...
Mizuki: Well, school can be a real drag sometimes...
Mizuki: But I get to watch my favorite anime and make videos about it, so I'd say I'm in a good place.
Mizuki's Sister: I see... That's good to hear.
Mizuki's Sister: Remember, I'm always here to listen if something does end up bothering you.
Mizuki's Sister: Especially since we won't get many chances to chat like this in the future.
Mizuki: Yeah, true...
Mizuki: Thanks, Sis! But I'm okay. There's nothing to worry about.
Mizuki: I'm just gonna do what I can to enjoy the present!
Mizuki's Sister: Okay...
Mizuki's Mother's Voice: Hey, you two, I bought some cake. Would you like to have some?
Mizuki: Oh, cake? Yes, please! Let's go, Sis!
Mizuki's Sister: ...
